Why does filing taxes feel like some kind of really annoying game show where we mostly can lose? If everyone already has all the numbers, why am I sitting around with the typewriter and software and a whole bunch of paper slips?
My tax lawyers are showing me how the system could work compared to how it does work and we as citizens should be outraged

Today, I brought six pieces of paper to a bank, only so she could print two more pieces, and then photocopy all eight pieces, for 16 total pages, to add one name and one contact piece of information to a file

Make me a bank where I can do 100% of the transactions of a normal Bank but be a hundred percent online and 24 by 7. And who else doesn't want that? Is anyone else eagerly hoping for someone to lock down the lobby?
People panic driving through a toll booth because they're told not to stop. Instead, they should wonder why it took them decades to do a very simple scan
Artificial reality would be a lot cooler if the information underneath it was real-time, live, and in any way reflected the real world that it could given all the systems
When even a basic pizza guy can't deliver because they can't keep the record straight on addresses in a small town and nowhere Ville Massachusetts, how do we even begin to trust anything bigger?

Digital transformation has nothing to do with getting your expense reports photograph is stuck in a file. It has everything to do with the distance between live and useful information versus the stupid idiotic stuff we all have to do everyday to survive
The world is a massive collection of inefficient, messy, physical world bound problems that shouldn't even be Glee exist in the world with $1,400 cell phones
If someone wants to Market to me, just give me information that's accurate

Do you know if people don't like marketers? Because there's almost never any documentation or numbers 2.2 that make any real sense. For so many people out there to be promising that a good video is going to change the world is starting to feel pretty damned irresponsible to me

Can you imagine all those containers just bobbing around out there in the ocean and stacked up in those parking areas because we somehow don't have the logistics in 2021 to move them? Do you know that you can buy some of those containers full of precious cargo for pennies?

I heard a guy in front of me at the drugstore being told that there was some possible allergic reaction with the medicine he was being given, and the guy says well the doctor told me about that. But if so, then why isn't that documented?

You know I the virus is going to kill Millions more people? Because the easier way to do things is just to go home again instead of Miss for different appointment because of stupid software that didn't know what time it was
Banks require specific humans with specific pieces of paper to visit at specific times in the universe where I can buy a building all by myself online with a few Mouse clicks

We collect and discard more real-time data than anyone knows what to do with, and we deliver the worst possible customer experience because we don't have anything vaguely resembling the real world made digital
The time for accurate live data is now. If your systems can't handle real-time, current, accurate information, then you should put up the boards over windows and take down your signs.
